ty, twenty years of fascism did alter the landscape of Italian cultural life. Among younger intellectuals in particular, the dictatorship left a legacy of practices and attitudes that often continued under different political rubrics after 1945.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aFascism and culturezItalyxHistory. 0aFascismzItalyxHistory. 0aFascismzItaly. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh  a20th century.  acultural history.  adictatorship.  aeconomic development.  aeurope.  aeuropean history.  afascism.  afascists.  ahistorical.  ahistory of culture.  ahistory of society.  ahistory students.  ahuman condition.  ainterwar history.  aitalian cinema.  aitalian culture.  aitaly.  alegacy of fascism.  amodel of modern world.  amodern historians.  amodern history.  amodernity.  amussolini.  anational identity.  anational traditions.  arevolution.  asocial boundaries.  asocial movements.  asocial status.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052024216640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093805240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520938052423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520938052/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY